comment_data.body:
This:

> Failed to connect to the VM observatory service at: ws://127.0.0.1:53074/JBcmmNfapt4=/ws
> java.io.IOException: Failed to connect: ws://127.0.0.1:53074/JBcmmNfapt4=/ws
> Caused by: de.roderick.weberknecht.WebSocketException: connection failed: unknown status code 302

Indicates to me that perhaps DDS has been enabled in the flutter repo - see the `status code 302` portion. cc @bkonyi 

You're on `d261f1ef58 (6 days ago)` - can you try syncing to another commit and see if that works?

Ben, if this is related to DDS, that likely indicates that the websocket library we're using in IntelliJ does not support http redirects. We can look for a different websocket library to use, but I think that generally we'll want to consider handing the DDS url to `flutter run` / `flutter test` clients by default. Happy to talk through the implications of that - to see if we can solve the edge cases w/ flutter attach and such.

> Ben, if this is related to DDS, that likely indicates that the websocket library we're using in IntelliJ does not support http redirects. We can look for a different websocket library to use, but I think that generally we'll want to consider handing the DDS url to `flutter run` / `flutter test` clients by default. Happy to talk through the implications of that - to see if we can solve the edge cases w/ flutter attach and such.

DDS shouldn't be enabled in the Flutter repo right now (it was disabled in https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/62508 12 days ago), so that shouldn't be it unless I disabled it incorrectly. Do you happen to have verbose logs @tvolkert? If DDS is enabled, it'll be mentioned in the logs. If it's not, there should be a warning message printed with a link to an issue.
This appears to happen when attempting to connect via Observatory as well.
Ah this is the one case I forgot to remove that Mehmet fixed in https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/62792. @tvolkert if you pull to a newer branch this should be resolved.

@bkonyi - thanks for looking into this!

@tvolkert - I did verify that I don't see this behavior on flutter master at head.
(closing old tabs). I verified that I can no longer repro this against ToT with updated plugin.  Thanks!
